definitions.definition: A premature explosion in the cylinder of a gas or oil engine during the exhaust or the compression stroke, tending to drive the piston in the wrong direction.
An explosion in the exhaust passages of an internal combustion engine .

main_definition: ( firefighting ) Alternative spelling of back fire .
